Merge pull request #3 from orlitzky/dairiki

Merge the remainder of Jeff Dairiki's "ipv6" branch

Merge the remainder of Jeff Dairiki's "ipv6" branch.

IPv6 support was originally added to rbldnsd by Jeff Dairiki in
v0.997. That code contains a Python (2.x) test suite that originally
expected Python to support IPv6. That is not always the case -- Python
can be compiled without IPv6 support. Since only the test suite
requires Python, it makes sense in that case to skip the (doomed) IPv6
portions of the test suite.

Jeff's "ipv6" branch contains further changes, not merged into the
official rbldbsd, to do just that. Those changes also address some
updates to the pydns API, and contain a fix for system-specific
weirdness with the gethostbyname() function.

These changes were discussed back in July and August of 2013:

http://www.corpit.ru/pipermail/rbldnsd/2013q3/001179.html
Fix for out of memory errors on huge zones. Thanks to Andrew Clayton
Small changes to the license files. Adding copy of GPL2
No need to check that the debian/ directory is still there
